  <!-- ============= INTRO ============= -->
  <section class="section-white">
    <div class="container intro-grid">
      <div class="intro-text">
        <h2>Thermador wall ovens in LA — what we actually see on service calls</h2>
        <p>Thermador invented the wall oven in 1947, and BSH Home Appliances (the Bosch-Siemens parent) has kept refining the platform ever since. What that means on the service side: the ovens themselves are overbuilt, the electronics are where things fail, and the failure patterns are predictable once you've seen enough of them.</p>

        <p>Our technicians run Thermador wall oven calls across the Westside and the foothills every single week. The Masterpiece Series units — ME301WS, MED301WS, and the combi-steam MED301JS — tend to fail on the touch-control panel around year 6 to 9. Not the heating elements, not the fan motors. The capacitive touch board gets flaky, you get a dead zone on the display, and suddenly you can't preheat. We've replaced enough of them to order the part before we even walk in the door, if the customer describes the symptom clearly on the phone.</p>

        <p>Professional Series ovens — POD301W, POD302W, PODS301W — have a different pattern. The heavy-duty bake element runs hotter than most, and in homes with rock-hard LA water where the self-clean cycle gets used a lot, the element lead wires cook off at the ceramic terminal. That's a $280–$340 repair, usually same-visit if we have the element on the van.</p>

        <p>Double wall ovens — MED302JS, ME302ES, POD302W — bring a specific question we hear constantly: "one cavity works, the other doesn't." Good news, that's almost always isolated: separate bake elements, separate thermostats, separate relays on most builds. We diagnose the failing cavity, fix it, and leave the working oven alone.</p>

        <p>The combi-steam units (MES301HP, MES301JP, MED301JS with steam function) are a category on their own — water reservoir sensors, steam generator calibration, descaling cycles that most homeowners have never run. When a Thermador combi-steam oven stops heating properly after year 4 or 5, nine times out of ten it's a scaled-up generator, not a failed component. We know the difference.</p>

        <p>Our diagnostic fee is $89, and it goes away the moment you approve the repair. We don't charge for holiday or evening appointments. What we quote on the driveway is what shows up on the invoice.</p>
      </div>

      <aside class="sticky-cta">
