  <!-- ============= COMMON PROBLEMS GRID ============= -->
  <section class="section-gray">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Thermador wall oven problems we repair — by symptom</h2>
      <p class="section-sub">The failures we see most on Masterpiece, Professional, and combi-steam wall ovens across Los Angeles.</p>
      <div class="problems-grid">
        <div class="problem-card">
          <h3>Oven not heating</h3>
          <p>Bake element burned out at the ceramic terminal, blown thermal fuse, or failed relay on the control board. Diagnosis starts with continuity on the element, then amperage at the bake circuit, then the board. Common across ME301WS, MED301WS, POD301W.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="problem-card">
          <h3>Uneven baking / hot spots</h3>
          <p>Convection fan motor dragging, bake and broil elements fighting each other, or oven sensor drifting out of spec. A half-inch gasket gap can shift cavity temperature by 25°F — we always check the door seal first before ordering parts.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="problem-card">
          <h3>Touch panel dead or flickering</h3>
          <p>Capacitive touch board failure — the signature Masterpiece issue at year 6–9. Dead zone on the display, unresponsive keys, or ghost touches. Replacement is a full panel assembly, order from BSH, usually 3–5 business days.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="problem-card">
          <h3>F1, F2, F3, E3 error codes</h3>
          <p>Each code points somewhere specific. F1 / F3 usually shorted or open oven sensor. F2 overheating — sensor, board, or relay welded. E3 on combi-steam means water system fault. We decode before we diagnose.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="problem-card">
          <h3>Oven door won't close / sagging</h3>
          <p>Door hinges wear after enough cycles. On heavy Thermador doors with the concealed hinge system, one failed hinge tilts the door and breaks the gasket seal. Pair replacement always — we never replace just one hinge.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="problem-card">
          <h3>Combi-steam oven not steaming</h3>
          <p>MES301HP, MES301JP, MED301JS steam-convection — water level sensor faulted, scale buildup on the steam generator, or clogged fill line. Descale + sensor clean solves 70% of these calls.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="problem-card">
          <h3>Self-clean won't start or stuck</h3>
          <p>Door latch motor failed, or the latch microswitch won't confirm. Thermador self-clean won't begin unless the door confirms fully locked. We replace the latch assembly and verify the clean cycle end-to-end.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="problem-card">
          <h3>Fan runs constantly after oven is off</h3>
          <p>Cooling blower thermistor stuck in "still hot" state, or the cooling relay welded closed. Easy fix once identified — but ignore it and the blower motor will burn out from continuous run.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============= POST-WARRANTY POSITIONING ============= -->
