      <div class="context-grid">
        <div class="context-item">
          <h3>Post-warranty specialists</h3>
          <p>We don't require a service contract. We come out once, diagnose, quote, fix. If you're out of the BSH warranty window, we're often the first call homeowners make — and the last, because most Thermador wall ovens we repair keep running for 5+ more years.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="context-item">
          <h3>Manufacturer-approved parts only</h3>
          <p>Every replacement part on a Thermador repair comes from a BSH-approved supply channel. No aftermarket bake elements, no generic control boards, no off-brand thermostats. Your warranty on the repair is only as good as the parts we install.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="context-item">
          <h3>Built-in protection</h3>
          <p>A Thermador wall oven is integrated into $20,000–$80,000 of custom cabinetry. Our installation protocol is non-invasive: we photograph the trim surround before we pull anything, mark the cabinet mounting points, and reinstall to factory tolerances. If your cabinet maker has to come back, that's on us — but in 15 years, they haven't had to.</p>
        </div>
