      <h2>Recent Thermador wall oven repairs — last 60 days</h2>
      <p class="section-sub">Real calls, real diagnoses, real fixes. Identifying details omitted.</p>

      <div class="cases-grid">
        <div class="case-card">
          <div class="case-meta">Beverly Hills · 90210 · MED302JS combi-steam double</div>
          <h3>"Upper oven heats, lower oven won't preheat past 200°F"</h3>
          <p>Classic lower-cavity bake element failure — the element was still showing continuity cold but opened under load. We confirmed with an amp clamp: 2.1 amps on the bake circuit when it should draw 15.8. Replaced the lower bake element with a BSH OEM part, recalibrated the lower sensor for good measure.</p>
          <p class="case-outcome">On-site 2 hours, $385 all-in including parts and labor. Customer was hosting that weekend — we booked for Thursday morning, done by lunch.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="case-card">
          <div class="case-meta">Brentwood · 90049 · ME301WS Masterpiece single</div>
          <h3>"Touch panel showing blank spots — can't set temperature"</h3>
          <p>Dead zones on the capacitive touch board — we see this every few weeks on Masterpiece units that hit year 7. Called BSH Van Nuys for the part, stocked locally. Pulled the trim surround, photographed the cabinet tolerance, swapped the touch-panel assembly, re-verified all cooking modes on first start.</p>
          <p class="case-outcome">Part was on-hand same-week. Total $475 including the panel assembly. Cabinet trim went back without a scratch.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="case-card">
