  <!-- ============= WHY US ============= -->
  <section class="section-gray">
    <div class="container why-grid">
      <div>
        <h2>Why homeowners with Thermador wall ovens call us first</h2>
        <p>We pick up the phone. Not a call center. Not a dispatcher reading from a script. When you call about a Thermador wall oven, someone who actually knows the platforms — and knows which models are likely to fail which way — picks up and talks you through it.</p>
        <p>Our technicians have spent 15+ years on Thermador built-in systems specifically. Not "appliance repair in general, Thermador occasionally." When we say Factory-Trained, we mean the ME301, POD301, MED301JS combi-steam, and the MES301 steam line are all platforms we service weekly — not quarterly.</p>
        <p>We don't push replacement. If your Thermador wall oven is 4 years old and the control board failed, we replace the board — not the oven. If it's 15 years old and the element terminal is corroded and the relays are chattering, we'll tell you honestly whether the repair makes sense or whether you're about to spend $800 on a unit that won't last another year.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="reviews-box">
        <h3>What customers say</h3>

