      <h2>Thermador wall oven repair FAQ</h2>
      <div class="faq-list">
        <details open>
          <summary>Do you repair both Masterpiece and Professional Series Thermador wall ovens?</summary>
          <p>Yes — every active Thermador built-in wall oven line. Masterpiece (ME301WS, MED301WS, MED301JS combi-steam), Professional Series (POD301W, POD302W, PODS301W), and the combi-steam Masterpiece units (MED301JS, MED302JS, MES301HP, MES301JP). Factory-trained on the BSH Home Appliances cooking platforms, which means ignition sequences, touch-panel calibration, convection airflow diagnostics, and steam-generator descaling are all in our standard playbook.</p>
        </details>
        <details>
          <summary>Can you service a Thermador wall oven after the factory warranty ends?</summary>
          <p>Yes — post-warranty service is our main lane. Most Thermador wall ovens we get called on are 3 to 12 years old, well past the factory window, and the homeowner just needs someone who knows the platform. We don't require a service contract, we use manufacturer-approved parts only, and we treat the built-in cabinetry the same way Factory-Certified Service would.</p>
        </details>
        <details>
          <summary>What does Thermador wall oven repair cost in Los Angeles?</summary>
          <p>Most Thermador wall oven repairs in the LA area fall in the $250–$500 range. Bake element, broil element, convection fan motor, and thermal fuse repairs land in the $275–$425 zone. Control board and touch-panel replacements on the MED301JS / MED302JS combi-steam units run $450–$680 because the panel assemblies are special-order. Every job starts with the $89 diagnostic, which is waived the moment you approve the repair.</p>
        </details>
        <details>
          <summary>Can you repair a double wall oven where only one cavity is failing?</summary>
          <p>Yes. On a Thermador double wall oven — MED302JS, ME302ES, POD302W, PODS302W — the upper and lower cavities have independent bake elements, sensors, thermostats, and in most builds independent control relays. We diagnose the failing cavity specifically, replace only what's bad in that cavity, and leave the working side untouched.</p>
        </details>
        <details>
          <summary>Do I need to pull the oven out of the cabinetry for diagnosis?</summary>
          <p>Usually no. Almost all Thermador wall-oven diagnostics — temperature calibration, door gasket, igniter (on dual-fuel Pro Harmony configurations), thermal fuse, bake and broil elements, control panel — can be done in place through the oven opening. We only pull the unit when the problem is behind the cavity, like a main wiring harness, rear thermostat, or cooling blower. When we do pull, we photograph the built-in trim first and reinstall to original factory tolerances.</p>
        </details>
        <details>
          <summary>Same-day Thermador wall oven repair — how fast, really?</summary>
          <p>If you call before 11 AM, our technician is usually at your door that afternoon across Beverly Hills, Bel Air, Brentwood, Santa Monica, West Hollywood, Malibu, Pacific Palisades, and Hancock Park. Pasadena and the east side run through our Pasadena branch at (626) 376-4458. For special-order parts like touch-panel assemblies or combi-steam control boards, we order from BSH and come back within 2–5 business days.</p>
        </details>
        <details>
          <summary>What warranty do you offer on Thermador wall oven repairs?</summary>
          <p>90 days on labor and 1 full year on manufacturer-approved parts — applied to every Thermador wall oven repair we do. If the exact same failure returns inside that window, we come back at no cost. No second diagnostic fee, no re-bill on the part.</p>
        </details>
